  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Mix the minced lamb, flaked salmon, grated carrot, grated cheddar cheese, chopped parsley, salt, and black pepper in a bowl.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix the garlic sauce, lemon juice, and olive oil.",
    "Place a cabbage leaf on a flat surface, with the stem end facing you.",
    "Place 1-2 tbsp of the lamb-salmon mixture in the center of the leaf, leaving a 2-inch border around it.",
    "Brush the edges with the garlic sauce mixture and fold the stem end over the filling, then fold in the sides and roll up the leaf to form a tight package, securing with a toothpick if needed.",
    "Repeat with the remaining leaves and filling.",
    "Place the packages seam-side down in a steamer basket and steam for 10-12 minutes, or until the cabbage is tender.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
